<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n26bfrf"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n26" href="#n26bfrf">N26 (VI.B.18)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n26all.htm#n26bfrf">back flyleaf recto(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> 1<sup>d</sup> black / Rowland Hill </blockquote> <dd class="well"><mm class="note">Note: The Penny Black was the world&apos;s first adhesive postage stamp used in a public postal system. It was first issued in the United Kingdom at the behest of Sir Rowland Hill (1795-1879) on 1 May 1840, but was not valid for use until 6 May. The stamp features a profile of Queen Victoria. </mm> </dd></dl>
